<% content_for(:title, "Chapter #{@chapter.position}: #{@chapter.title} — #{@book.title}") %>

<%= render "shared/page_header" %>

<div class="flex flex-col gap-10 lg:flex-row lg:items-start lg:gap-12">
  <%= render "toc", chapters: @chapters, active_chapter: @chapter.position %>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm sm:p-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
      <%= link_to "Overview", books_book_path(@book), class: "font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500" %>
      <span class="mx-1 text-slate-300" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span class="text-slate-600">Chapter <%= @chapter.position %> of <%= @book.chapters.size %></span>
    </p>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
      <%= @chapter.title %>
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-8 max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
        This is mock body copy for chapter <%= @chapter.position %>. Imagine a trusted operator leaning in during cleanup and
        saying: “Here’s what actually matters about <%= @chapter.title.downcase %>—ignore the influencer stuff.”
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">The short version</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        You win when defaults are boring: the critical checklist lives in one place, handoffs don’t fight each other,
        and the numbers get read on the same day every week. This chapter gathers those defaults into
        a single page your leads can riff on—not a binder nobody opens.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Three decisions to lock</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 list-inside list-decimal space-y-2 leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        <li>What metric you glance at daily (throughput, ticket, waste—pick one).</li>
        <li>Who owns the checklist when the owner isn’t on the floor.</li>
        <li>What you refuse to expand until margins are proven.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Try this on Monday</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        Block fifteen minutes before open. Walk the line a customer would walk: first impression, clarity, friction, and the
        small ugly details. Fix the first thing you see with what you already have on hand—no “we’ll order that later” unless
        safety demands it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">If you only remember one line</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 rounded-xl border border-indigo-100 bg-indigo-50/80 px-4 py-3 text-indigo-950 leading-relaxed">
        Consistency beats cleverness: people notice when the experience feels calm and reliable, not when you added a fourth
        shiny idea nobody uses.
      </p>
    </div>

    <nav class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8 text-sm font-medium" aria-label="Chapter pagination">
      <% ch_index = @chapters.index(@chapter) %>
      <% prev_ch = ch_index && ch_index.positive? ? @chapters[ch_index - 1] : nil %>
      <% if prev_ch && !chapter_locked?(prev_ch) %>
        <%= link_to "← Previous chapter",
              books_book_chapter_path(@book, prev_ch.position),
              class: "text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500" %>
      <% elsif prev_ch %>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-slate-400" aria-disabled="true" title="Subscribe to unlock">
          <%= heroicon "lock-closed", variant: :mini, options: { class: "h-4 w-4", "aria-hidden": true } %>
          <span>Previous chapter locked</span>
        </span>
      <% else %>
        <span class="text-slate-400">← Previous chapter</span>
      <% end %>

      <% next_ch = ch_index && ch_index < @chapters.size - 1 ? @chapters[ch_index + 1] : nil %>
      <% if next_ch && !chapter_locked?(next_ch) %>
        <%= link_to "Next chapter →",
              books_book_chapter_path(@book, next_ch.position),
              class: "text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500" %>
      <% elsif next_ch %>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-slate-400" aria-disabled="true" title="Subscribe to unlock">
          <span>Next chapter locked</span>
          <%= heroicon "lock-closed", variant: :mini, options: { class: "h-4 w-4", "aria-hidden": true } %>
        </span>
      <% else %>
        <span class="text-slate-400">Next chapter →</span>
      <% end %>
    </nav>
  </article>
</div>
